The paper focuses on machine intelligence (MI) applications and optimizing their workloads on GPUs. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). However, since the paper specifically focuses on GPU caching policies, cs.AR and cs.AI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DC, cs.NE, and cs.CV.
